      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Which of the following compounds can exist as pairs of cis–trans isomers? Draw each pair, and indicate the geometry of each isomer.</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b> CH<sub>3</sub>CH<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CH<sub>2</sub> <b>(b)</b> (CH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CHCH<sub>3</sub> <b>(c)</b> CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CHCH<sub>3</sub> <b>(d)</b> (CH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>C<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>C(CH<sub>3</sub>)CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub><br><b>(e)</b> ClCH<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CHCl <b>(f)</b> BrCH<span data-math=\"\\text{=}\"></span>CHCl</p> \n",
